Want received his BA in computer science from Churchill College, Cambridge University, UK in 1983 and continued research at Cambridge into reliable distributed multimedia-systems. He earned a PhD in 1988. While at Olivetti Research (1988-91) he developed the Active Badge, a system for automatically locating people in a building. He joined Xerox PARC's Ubiquitous Computing program in 1991 and lead a project called PARCTab, one of the first context-aware computer systems. At PARC Want managed the Embedded Systems group and earned the position of Principal Scientist. A more complete summary of his work can be found at www.ubicomp.com/want.